{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1134,"text":"This is a painting from the 16th century\nfrom Lucas Cranach the Elder."},{"time":6160,"text":"It shows the famous Fountain of Youth."},{"time":9308,"text":"If you drink its water or you bathe in it,\nyou will get health and youth."},{"time":15857,"text":"Every culture, every civilization\nhas dreamed of finding eternal youth."},{"time":22044,"text":"There are people like Alexander the Great\nor Ponce De Le√≥n, the explorer,"},{"time":26820,"text":"who spent much of their life\nchasing the Fountain of Youth."},{"time":30726,"text":"They didn't find it."},{"time":33450,"text":"But what if there was something to it?"},{"time":36074,"text":"What if there was something\nto this Fountain of Youth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39284,"text":"I will share an absolutely amazing\ndevelopment in aging research"},{"time":44486,"text":"that could revolutionize\nthe way we think about aging"},{"time":48120,"text":"and how we may treat age-related\ndiseases in the future."},{"time":52145,"text":"It started with experiments that showed,"},{"time":54678,"text":"in a recent number\nof studies about growing,"},{"time":57996,"text":"that animals -- old mice --\nthat share a blood supply with young mice"},{"time":64021,"text":"can get rejuvenated."},{"time":66148,"text":"This is similar to what you might see\nin humans, in Siamese twins,"},{"time":70781,"text":"and I know this sounds a bit creepy."},{"time":73338,"text":"But what Tom Rando, a stem-cell\nresearcher, reported in 2007,"},{"time":79309,"text":"was that old muscle from a mouse\ncan be rejuvenated"},{"time":82833,"text":"if it's exposed to young blood\nthrough common circulation."},{"time":87903,"text":"This was reproduced by Amy Wagers\nat Harvard a few years later,"},{"time":92570,"text":"and others then showed that similar\nrejuvenating effects could be observed"},{"time":97189,"text":"in the pancreas, the liver and the heart."},{"time":100974,"text":"But what I'm most excited about,\nand several other labs as well,"},{"time":105095,"text":"is that this may even apply to the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108715,"text":"So, what we found is that an old mouse\nexposed to a young environment"},{"time":114070,"text":"in this model called parabiosis,"},{"time":117107,"text":"shows a younger brain --"},{"time":118923,"text":"and a brain that functions better."},{"time":121966,"text":"And I repeat:"},{"time":123580,"text":"an old mouse that gets young blood\nthrough shared circulation"},{"time":129817,"text":"looks younger and functions\nyounger in its brain."},{"time":133998,"text":"So when we get older --"},{"time":135554,"text":"we can look at different aspects\nof human cognition,"},{"time":138250,"text":"and you can see on this slide here,"},{"time":140027,"text":"we can look at reasoning,\nverbal ability and so forth."},{"time":143899,"text":"And up to around age 50 or 60,\nthese functions are all intact,"},{"time":149202,"text":"and as I look at the young audience\nhere in the room, we're all still fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153708,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154740,"text":"But it's scary to see\nhow all these curves go south."},{"time":158571,"text":"And as we get older,"},{"time":160184,"text":"diseases such as Alzheimer's\nand others may develop."},{"time":165004,"text":"We know that with age,\nthe connections between neurons --"},{"time":168599,"text":"the way neurons talk to each other,\nthe synapses -- they start to deteriorate;"},{"time":173274,"text":"neurons die, the brain starts to shrink,"},{"time":176604,"text":"and there's an increased susceptibility\nfor these neurodegenerative diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181573,"text":"One big problem we have -- to try\nto understand how this really works"},{"time":186506,"text":"at a very molecular mechanistic level --"},{"time":189126,"text":"is that we can't study the brains\nin detail, in living people."},{"time":194033,"text":"We can do cognitive tests,\nwe can do imaging --"},{"time":197043,"text":"all kinds of sophisticated testing."},{"time":199763,"text":"But we usually have to wait\nuntil the person dies"},{"time":203405,"text":"to get the brain and look at how it really\nchanged through age or in a disease."},{"time":208888,"text":"This is what neuropathologists\ndo, for example."},{"time":212333,"text":"So, how about we think of the brain\nas being part of the larger organism."},{"time":218024,"text":"Could we potentially understand more"},{"time":220525,"text":"about what happens in the brain\nat the molecular level"},{"time":223478,"text":"if we see the brain\nas part of the entire body?"},{"time":227088,"text":"So if the body ages or gets sick,\ndoes that affect the brain?"},{"time":231989,"text":"And vice versa: as the brain gets older,\ndoes that influence the rest of the body?"},{"time":237050,"text":"And what connects all the different\ntissues in the body"},{"time":240565,"text":"is blood."},{"time":242366,"text":"Blood is the tissue that not only carries\ncells that transport oxygen, for example,"},{"time":248215,"text":"the red blood cells,"},{"time":249480,"text":"or fights infectious diseases,"},{"time":251704,"text":"but it also carries messenger molecules,"},{"time":255999,"text":"hormone-like factors\nthat transport information"},{"time":259935,"text":"from one cell to another,\nfrom one tissue to another,"},{"time":264092,"text":"including the brain."},{"time":265573,"text":"So if we look at how the blood\nchanges in disease or age,"},{"time":270735,"text":"can we learn something about the brain?"},{"time":273651,"text":"We know that as we get older,\nthe blood changes as well,"},{"time":278511,"text":"so these hormone-like factors\nchange as we get older."},{"time":281494,"text":"And by and large,\nfactors that we know are required"},{"time":285717,"text":"for the development of tissues,\nfor the maintenance of tissues --"},{"time":289162,"text":"they start to decrease as we get older,"},{"time":292063,"text":"while factors involved in repair,\nin injury and in inflammation --"},{"time":296790,"text":"they increase as we get older."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298764,"text":"So there's this unbalance of good\nand bad factors, if you will."},{"time":304988,"text":"And to illustrate what we can do\npotentially with that,"},{"time":308005,"text":"I want to talk you through\nan experiment that we did."},{"time":310681,"text":"We had almost 300 blood samples\nfrom healthy human beings"},{"time":314354,"text":"20 to 89 years of age,"},{"time":316895,"text":"and we measured over 100\nof these communication factors,"},{"time":320814,"text":"these hormone-like proteins that\ntransport information between tissues."},{"time":325266,"text":"And what we noticed first"},{"time":326966,"text":"is that between the youngest\nand the oldest group,"},{"time":329807,"text":"about half the factors\nchanged significantly."},{"time":333128,"text":"So our body lives in a very\ndifferent environment as we get older,"},{"time":336287,"text":"when it comes to these factors."},{"time":338062,"text":"And using statistical\nor bioinformatics programs,"},{"time":341582,"text":"we could try to discover\nthose factors that best predict age --"},{"time":346300,"text":"in a way, back-calculate\nthe relative age of a person."},{"time":350337,"text":"And the way this looks\nis shown in this graph."},{"time":353618,"text":"So, on the one axis you see\nthe actual age a person lived,"},{"time":359011,"text":"the chronological age."},{"time":360340,"text":"So, how many years they lived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362086,"text":"And then we take these top factors\nthat I showed you,"},{"time":364818,"text":"and we calculate their relative age,\ntheir biological age."},{"time":370708,"text":"And what you see is that\nthere is a pretty good correlation,"},{"time":374366,"text":"so we can pretty well predict\nthe relative age of a person."},{"time":377705,"text":"But what's really exciting\nare the outliers,"},{"time":381644,"text":"as they so often are in life."},{"time":383922,"text":"You can see here, the person\nI highlighted with the green dot"},{"time":388514,"text":"is about 70 years of age"},{"time":391134,"text":"but seems to have a biological age,\nif what we're doing here is really true,"},{"time":396164,"text":"of only about 45."},{"time":398231,"text":"So is this a person that actually\nlooks much younger than their age?"},{"time":402183,"text":"But more importantly: Is this a person\nwho is maybe at a reduced risk"},{"time":406723,"text":"to develop an age-related disease\nand will have a long life --"},{"time":410071,"text":"will live to 100 or more?"},{"time":412402,"text":"On the other hand, the person here,\nhighlighted with the red dot,"},{"time":416987,"text":"is not even 40,\nbut has a biological age of 65."},{"time":421917,"text":"Is this a person at an increased risk\nof developing an age-related disease?"},{"time":426339,"text":"So in our lab, we're trying\nto understand these factors better,"},{"time":430019,"text":"and many other groups\nare trying to understand,"},{"time":432281,"text":"what are the true aging factors,"},{"time":434381,"text":"and can we learn something about them\nto possibly predict age-related diseases?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":440281,"text":"So what I've shown you so far\nis simply correlational, right?"},{"time":444367,"text":"You can just say,\n\"Well, these factors change with age,\""},{"time":448422,"text":"but you don't really know\nif they do something about aging."},{"time":453031,"text":"So what I'm going to show you now\nis very remarkable"},{"time":456103,"text":"and it suggests that these factors\ncan actually modulate the age of a tissue."},{"time":461845,"text":"And that's where we come back\nto this model called parabiosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465167,"text":"So, parabiosis is done in mice"},{"time":467731,"text":"by surgically connecting\nthe two mice together,"},{"time":472667,"text":"and that leads then\nto a shared blood system,"},{"time":475024,"text":"where we can now ask,\n\"How does the old brain get influenced"},{"time":479835,"text":"by exposure to the young blood?\""},{"time":482144,"text":"And for this purpose, we use young mice"},{"time":484372,"text":"that are an equivalency\nof 20-year-old people,"},{"time":487849,"text":"and old mice that are roughly\n65 years old in human years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492958,"text":"What we found is quite remarkable."},{"time":495808,"text":"We find there are more neural stem cells\nthat make new neurons"},{"time":499552,"text":"in these old brains."},{"time":501351,"text":"There's an increased\nactivity of the synapses,"},{"time":503957,"text":"the connections between neurons."},{"time":506020,"text":"There are more genes expressed\nthat are known to be involved"},{"time":509329,"text":"in the formation of new memories."},{"time":511659,"text":"And there's less of this bad inflammation."},{"time":515427,"text":"But we observed that there are no cells\nentering the brains of these animals."},{"time":521947,"text":"So when we connect them,"},{"time":523357,"text":"there are actually no cells\ngoing into the old brain, in this model."},{"time":529379,"text":"Instead, we've reasoned, then,\nthat it must be the soluble factors,"},{"time":533064,"text":"so we could collect simply the soluble\nfraction of blood which is called plasma,"},{"time":537871,"text":"and inject either young plasma\nor old plasma into these mice,"},{"time":541839,"text":"and we could reproduce\nthese rejuvenating effects,"},{"time":544231,"text":"but what we could also do now"},{"time":545969,"text":"is we could do memory tests with mice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548443,"text":"As mice get older, like us humans,\nthey have memory problems."},{"time":552818,"text":"It's just harder to detect them,"},{"time":554435,"text":"but I'll show you in a minute\nhow we do that."},{"time":556803,"text":"But we wanted to take this\none step further,"},{"time":559522,"text":"one step closer to potentially\nbeing relevant to humans."},{"time":563586,"text":"What I'm showing you now\nare unpublished studies,"},{"time":566807,"text":"where we used human plasma,\nyoung human plasma,"},{"time":571364,"text":"and as a control, saline,"},{"time":573237,"text":"and injected it into old mice,"},{"time":575137,"text":"and asked, can we again\nrejuvenate these old mice?"},{"time":580013,"text":"Can we make them smarter?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":582104,"text":"And to do this, we used a test.\nIt's called a Barnes maze."},{"time":585417,"text":"This is a big table\nthat has lots of holes in it,"},{"time":588596,"text":"and there are guide marks around it,"},{"time":592103,"text":"and there's a bright light,\nas on this stage here."},{"time":594733,"text":"The mice hate this and they try to escape,"},{"time":597890,"text":"and find the single hole that you see\npointed at with an arrow,"},{"time":602170,"text":"where a tube is mounted underneath"},{"time":604139,"text":"where they can escape\nand feel comfortable in a dark hole."},{"time":607977,"text":"So we teach them, over several days,"},{"time":609803,"text":"to find this space\non these cues in the space,"},{"time":612730,"text":"and you can compare this for humans,"},{"time":615548,"text":"to finding your car in a parking lot\nafter a busy day of shopping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619802,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620827,"text":"Many of us have probably had\nsome problems with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624602,"text":"So, let's look at an old mouse here."},{"time":626954,"text":"This is an old mouse\nthat has memory problems,"},{"time":629154,"text":"as you'll notice in a moment."},{"time":631305,"text":"It just looks into every hole,\nbut it didn't form this spacial map"},{"time":636053,"text":"that would remind it where it was\nin the previous trial or the last day."},{"time":641873,"text":"In stark contrast, this mouse here\nis a sibling of the same age,"},{"time":647364,"text":"but it was treated with young\nhuman plasma for three weeks,"},{"time":652807,"text":"with small injections every three days."},{"time":655741,"text":"And as you noticed, it almost\nlooks around, \"Where am I?\" --"},{"time":659988,"text":"and then walks straight\nto that hole and escapes."},{"time":662919,"text":"So, it could remember where that hole was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666742,"text":"So by all means, this old mouse\nseems to be rejuvenated --"},{"time":670454,"text":"it functions more like a younger mouse."},{"time":672857,"text":"And it also suggests\nthat there is something"},{"time":675587,"text":"not only in young mouse plasma,\nbut in young human plasma"},{"time":680602,"text":"that has the capacity\nto help this old brain."},{"time":684834,"text":"So to summarize,"},{"time":686010,"text":"we find the old mouse, and its brain\nin particular, are malleable."},{"time":690233,"text":"They're not set in stone;\nwe can actually change them."},{"time":693708,"text":"It can be rejuvenated."},{"time":695680,"text":"Young blood factors can reverse aging,"},{"time":698301,"text":"and what I didn't show you --"},{"time":700037,"text":"in this model, the young mouse actually\nsuffers from exposure to the old."},{"time":705283,"text":"So there are old-blood factors\nthat can accelerate aging."},{"time":709725,"text":"And most importantly,\nhumans may have similar factors,"},{"time":714066,"text":"because we can take young human\nblood and have a similar effect."},{"time":718592,"text":"Old human blood, I didn't show you,\ndoes not have this effect;"},{"time":722172,"text":"it does not make the mice younger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725071,"text":"So, is this magic transferable to humans?"},{"time":728723,"text":"We're running a small\nclinical study at Stanford,"},{"time":732376,"text":"where we treat Alzheimer's patients\nwith mild disease"},{"time":736276,"text":"with a pint of plasma\nfrom young volunteers, 20-year-olds,"},{"time":742910,"text":"and do this once a week for four weeks,"},{"time":745529,"text":"and then we look\nat their brains with imaging."},{"time":749050,"text":"We test them cognitively,"},{"time":750918,"text":"and we ask their caregivers\nfor daily activities of living."},{"time":754948,"text":"What we hope is that there are\nsome signs of improvement"},{"time":758891,"text":"from this treatment."},{"time":760758,"text":"And if that's the case,\nthat could give us hope"},{"time":763338,"text":"that what I showed you works in mice"},{"time":765782,"text":"might also work in humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768478,"text":"Now, I don't think we will live forever."},{"time":771955,"text":"But maybe we discovered"},{"time":774316,"text":"that the Fountain of Youth\nis actually within us,"},{"time":777427,"text":"and it has just dried out."},{"time":779574,"text":"And if we can turn it\nback on a little bit,"},{"time":782426,"text":"maybe we can find the factors\nthat are mediating these effects,"},{"time":787077,"text":"we can produce these factors synthetically"},{"time":789688,"text":"and we can treat diseases of aging,\nsuch as Alzheimer's disease"},{"time":793725,"text":"or other dementias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795282,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796457,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}